dump_histogram_view(25.10)                          dump_histogram_view(25.10)

Name
       dump_histogram_view - Saves (dumps) the image of the histogram shown in
       Global Timing Debug automatically during the process

Syntax
       dump_histogram_view

       [-help]

       -name <string>

       [-type <string>]

       Saves  (dumps)  the image of the histogram shown in Global Timing Debug
       automatically during the process.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each dump_histogram_view parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man dump_histogram_view.

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of the image file to save the histogram.

       -type <string>
              Specifies the type of file (image format) to be  saved.  Options
              are bmp/jpg/gif/ppm/tif/csv.

              Default: bmp

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

